Additional Notes

Platinum Coins are extremely rare and usually only used by nobles, powerful merchants, or for large transactions (buying land, ships, or magical artifacts).
Most common people only ever use Copper and Silver. Gold is considered “wealthy person’s money.”
Many border regions and smaller villages still use barter alongside coins.
The Azure Accord (Merchant Guild) controls much of the official minting and tries to maintain stable exchange rates, but in war-torn areas, inflation and coin clipping are common problems.
Counterfeit coins (especially silver and gold) are a frequent issue, particularly near demonic borders.

Quick Conversion Table

